tourBios.curYrHigh: Lost in a playoff for fully-exempt status at the 2014 California Qualifying Tournament...In first career PGA TOUR Canada start at the season-opening PC Financial Open, held the 54-hole lead, thanks to a Point Grey G&CC course record of 11-under-par 61 in the third round. The bogey-free 61, the lowest round on PGA TOUR Canada since 2012, included 11 birdies. Entered the final round with a one-stroke lead over Brad Clapp but closed with a 2-over-par 74 to finish T7.
tourBios.carHigh: Has one runner-up finish on the eGolf Tour. 2011: Made his Web.com Tour debut, at the Melwood Prince George's County Open (missed the cut).
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Won the 2008 U.S. Public Links Championship to earn an invitation to the 2009 Masters Tournament (missed the cut)...Finished T39 at the 2009 John Deere Classic on the PGA TOUR...Three-time, second-team All-Big Ten selection...Owns three career individual wins while at Michigan State, where he was a three-time Academic All-Big Ten.
tourBios.personal: Brother, Dave, played basketball at both Northwestern University and Drake University.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the PGA TOUR Canada was T7th in 2014 at the PC Financial Open.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks T85th in Total Eagles on the PGA TOUR Canada.
